🏗️ Epic 1: Project Scaffolding & Infrastructure
Goal: Set up the environment and remote storage.

Story: Initialize Repository and Environment
    Task: Create GitHub repository with .gitignore (Python/venv).
    Task: Set up a virtual environment and install prefect, sqlalchemy, requests, and python-dotenv.
Story: Provision Remote Database
    Task: Create a free-tier Postgres instance on Aiven
    Task: Verify connection using a DB client DBeaver
Story: Database Schema Design
    Task: Create fact table crypt_prices (unique constrain on timestamp, currency)
    Task: Create dimension table currencies (initiate it with BTC, ETH, SOL, XRP, BNB, ADA)

--------------------------------------------------

🐍 Epic 2: Data Engineering (The ETL)
Goal: Build the core logic for fetching and saving data.

Story: API Extraction Logic
    Task: Get the API endpoint from Binance
    Task: Write a Python function to fetch prices for a list of coins
Story: Data Transformation & Validation
    Task: Create a data model (using Pydantic or a simple Dict) to standardize the API response.
    Task: Ensure timestamps are converted to UTC ISO format.
Story: Database Load Logic
    Task: Write an "Upsert" function using SQLAlchemy to insert data into Postgres.
    Task: Implement error handling for database connection timeouts.

--------------------------------------------------

🚀 Epic 3: Orchestration with Prefect
Goal: Turn the script into a reliable, scheduled pipeline.

Story: Convert Script to Prefect Flow
    Task: Decorate extraction and loading functions as @task.
    Task: Create a main @flow to link the tasks together.
Story: Resilience and Retries
    Task: Configure retries and retry_delay_seconds on the API task to handle network blips.
    Task: Add logging to track successful vs. failed runs.
Story: Scheduling
    Task: Implement a 1-minute interval schedule using Prefect’s deployment settings or flow.serve().

📦 Epic 4: Containerization & Deployment
Goal: Make the project portable and "production-ready."

Story: Dockerize the Application
    Task: Write a Dockerfile using a slim Python base image.
    Task: Create a docker-compose.yml to manage environment variables safely.
Story: Local Deployment Test
    Task: Run the entire pipeline inside a Docker container and monitor the remote DB for updates.
Story: (Bonus) GitHub Actions CI
    Task: Create a workflow to lint the code (Flake8/Black) on every push.

📝 Epic 5: Documentation & Presentation
Goal: Sell the project to a hiring manager.

Story: The Ultimate README
    Task: Create an Architecture Diagram (using Mermaid.js or Excalidraw).
    Task: Write "How to Run" instructions.
    Task: Add a section on "Future Improvements" (e.g., adding a Grafana dashboard).
Story: Final Cleanup
    Task: Remove any hardcoded secrets.
    Task: Record a 30-second GIF or take a screenshot of the Prefect UI showing successful runs.